# React Component Rules

## Component Structure

### Standard Component Template
```tsx
import { type ComponentProps } from 'react';
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

interface ButtonProps extends ComponentProps<'button'> {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'ghost';
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
  isLoading?: boolean;
}

export function Button({
  variant = 'primary',
  size = 'md',
  isLoading = false,
  className,
  children,
  disabled,
  ...props
}: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        'inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md font-medium transition-colors',
        'focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-2',
        'disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50',
        {
          'bg-primary text-white hover:bg-primary/90': variant === 'primary',
          'bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary/80': variant === 'secondary',
          'hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground': variant === 'ghost',
          'h-8 px-3 text-sm': size === 'sm',
          'h-10 px-4': size === 'md',
          'h-12 px-6 text-lg': size === 'lg',
        },
        className
      )}
      disabled={disabled || isLoading}
      {...props}
    >
      {isLoading ? (
        <span className="mr-2 h-4 w-4 animate-spin rounded-full border-2 border-current border-t-transparent" />
      ) : null}
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}
```

## Component Categories

### `/components/ui/` — Base Components
Primitive, reusable components with no business logic:
- Button, Input, Select, Checkbox
- Card, Dialog, Dropdown
- Typography (Heading, Text, Label)

### `/components/features/` — Feature Components
Business logic components specific to features:
- UserProfile, TaskList, ProjectCard
- AuthForm, SettingsPanel

### `/components/layouts/` — Layout Components
Page structure and navigation:
- Header, Footer, Sidebar
- PageContainer, DashboardLayout

## Props Patterns

### Extending HTML Elements
```tsx
// Extend the native element props
interface InputProps extends ComponentProps<'input'> {
  label?: string;
  error?: string;
}
```

### Polymorphic Components
```tsx
interface BoxProps<T extends React.ElementType> {
  as?: T;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}

export function Box<T extends React.ElementType = 'div'>({
  as,
  children,
  ...props
}: BoxProps<T> & Omit<ComponentProps<T>, keyof BoxProps<T>>) {
  const Component = as || 'div';
  return <Component {...props}>{children}</Component>;
}
```

## Styling with Tailwind

### Use the `cn` Helper
```tsx
// lib/utils.ts
import { clsx, type ClassValue } from 'clsx';
import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';

export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {
  return twMerge(clsx(inputs));
}
```

### Conditional Classes
```tsx
<div
  className={cn(
    'base-classes',
    isActive && 'active-classes',
    {
      'variant-a': variant === 'a',
      'variant-b': variant === 'b',
    }
  )}
/>
```

## State Management

### Local State (useState)
Use for UI state that doesn't need to be shared:
```tsx
const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
```

### Form State (useForm)
Use react-hook-form for complex forms:
```tsx
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';

const { register, handleSubmit, formState: { errors } } = useForm();
```

### Server State (Convex)
Use Convex hooks for server data:
```tsx
const data = useQuery(api.tasks.list);
const createTask = useMutation(api.tasks.create);
```

## Accessibility (MUST)

### Required Patterns
```tsx
// Buttons must have accessible names
<button aria-label="Close dialog">
  <XIcon />
</button>

// Form inputs must have labels
<label htmlFor="email">Email</label>
<input id="email" type="email" />

// Images must have alt text
<img src={url} alt="Description of image" />

// Interactive elements need focus states
className="focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-2"
```

### Keyboard Navigation
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Use proper focus management in modals/dialogs
- Support Escape key to close overlays

## Performance Patterns

### Memoization (Use Sparingly)
```tsx
// Only memo expensive computations
const expensiveValue = useMemo(() => computeExpensive(data), [data]);

// Only useCallback when passing to memoized children
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  // handler logic
}, [dependency]);
```

### Lazy Loading
```tsx
import dynamic from 'next/dynamic';

const HeavyComponent = dynamic(() => import('./HeavyComponent'), {
  loading: () => <Skeleton />,
});
```

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

❌ **Don't** use `index` as key for lists that can reorder
❌ **Don't** mutate state directly
❌ **Don't** use `useEffect` for derived state (use `useMemo`)
❌ **Don't** over-use `useCallback`/`useMemo` (trust React's speed)
❌ **Don't** put business logic in UI components (extract to hooks/utils)
❌ **Don't** use `any` type for props
